headline: Fed Rate Move, Apple Earnings, Trump-Xi Meeting: What to Watch Next Week
summary: Investors next week will tune into big-tech earnings and the first Federal Reserve meeting since the U.S. government shutdown began. Later in the week, President Trump is due to meet with Chinese leader Xi Jinping as trade tensions between the two economic giants simmer.

headline: Stablecoin volumes triple Visa’s as a16z projects digital dollars to hit $3tn by 2030
summary: The sector sees $46 trillion in annual transactions. Transaction volume for September hit $1.25 trillion. Expected to grow 104 times by 2030, according to a16z.

headline: 2 Large-Cap Stocks to Keep an Eye On and 1 We Avoid
summary: Large-cap stocks have the power to shape entire industries thanks to their size and widespread influence. With such vast footprints, however, finding new areas for growth is much harder than for smaller, more agile players.
